Musician Sanaipei Tande and Swahili RnB heartthrob Otile Brown have released a love ballad together, which has set tongues wagging over the visible onset chemistry between the two. The song titled Chaguo la Moyo Wangu, captures the two singers as a couple declaring their undying love for each other on their wedding day. Sanaipei wears an off shoulder mermaid wedding gown while Otile Brown looks dapper in a navy blue suit. Social media has been abuzz with speculation ever since pictures of the two in a wedding setting emerged online. The two are have neither denied nor confirmed if they really got hitched in a secret wedding. The song is produced by Teddy B, and directed by X Antony.